INDIA’S FIRST CONNECTOR COMPANY





                    ALLIED IS A PROUD SUPPLIER TO THE INDIAN DEFENCE





                   ALLIED IS AN APPROVED SUPPLIER TO THE INDIAN RAILWAYS





                   ALLIED CONNECTORS ARE USED IN THE POWER SECTOR – THERMAL, HYDRO AND NUCLEAR





                   ALLIED CONNECTORS ARE APPROVED FOR USE ON MILITARY VEHICLES AND MILITARY EQUIPMENT





                   ALLIED CONNECTORS ARE USED IN CAR ASSEMBLY ROBOTICS, TEST EQUIPMENT, AND IN MANY OTHER APPLICATIONS…








Welcome to Allied Connectors
Allied Electronics Corporation, popularly known as ‘Allied Connectors’, is a manufacturer of circular multi-pin military connectors (as per various MIL specifications) based in Mumbai, India.

	Allied’s proven performance over nearly half a century of quality, reliability, and service has made it a preferred supplier for connectors used in the most demanding of applications, like  
Defence  | Railways |  Process Control Electronics  |  CNC Machines  |  Light & Sound industry  | Power Plants... 
More



Who we are



Established in 1966
Manufacturing a wide range of interconnection products
Specialist in circular multipin connectors


More



Our Products




More



Our Applications



Defence
Railways
Process Control Electronics
CNC Machines, Robotics, Servo Drives
Light & Sound industry
Power Plants


More







Qualifications & Approvals


NEW! Allied MS and MG range have been tested and certified as ‘CE’ compliant
NEW! A flame retardant version of Polychloroprene insulating material available, conforming to UL 94 V-0
ISO 9001:2008 certified company
Range MS, Range MG, Range Russian/Metric qualification approval by LCSO – Ministry of Defence, Government of India
Approved as a supplier to Indian Railways by R.D.S.O (Research Design and Standards Organisation)
Approved supplier to Siemens, Caterpillar, Cummins, and many other MNC’s operating in India
Halogen-free flame-retardant insulator material conforms to French standard NF F 16-101 classification 12F1 and British specification BS 6853app. A clause A.9 and app. B clause B.5.1
RoHS compliant finishes approved by TUV 
IP65, IP68 performance on select connectors, approved by ERTL





